  "prompt": "It goes without saying that money laundering is illegal, doesn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, **money laundering** is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or other crimes) appear legitimate by disguising its origins. This is typically done by funneling the funds through a series of transactions or financial systems to obscure their illicit source.\n\nGovernments and international organizations have established strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering, such as the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**, which sets global standards for anti-money laundering (AML) efforts. Penalties for money laundering can include substantial fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment, depending on the severity of the offense and the jurisdiction.\n\nSo, it absolutely **goes without saying**\u2014money laundering is a serious crime with severe consequences.",
